
// This Hyperlambda code snippet uses the [strings.replace] slot to replace occurrences of a specific substring within a string node. It targets the node specified by the expression [@.result], replacing all occurrences of the substring defined in the [follow_up] node with the string "true". This operation is useful for dynamically altering string content based on specific conditions or inputs.
strings.replace:x:@.result
   .:[[follow_up]]
   .:true
